E(X\mid Y)(y)
X
Y
E(X|Y)(y) = \sum_x{xP(X\mid Y)}=\frac{\sum_xxP(X=x, Y=y)}{P(Y=y)},
E(X|Y)(y) = \frac{1\cdot P(1, Y=y)}{P(Y=y)} + \frac{2\cdot P(2, Y=y)}{P(Y=y)} + \dots + \frac{6\cdot P(6, Y=y)}{P(Y=y)}.
E(X\mid Y)=\frac12Y.
P(X=3,Y=y) = 0
y \leq 3
P(X=3, Y=y) = P(X=3,\textrm{second die displays a y-3}) = 1/36 \quad
y>3
